<item>   Manson, Joseph H., Wrangham, Richard W. 1991. Intergroup aggression in chimpanzees and humans. Current Anthropology. 32: 369-390.
      <para id="id1168597106361">This article examines the similarities in intergroup aggression in humans and chimpanzees, a cross-species comparison. It addresses the questions of under what circumstances is intergroup aggression favored by evolution, why are males the main actors in intergroup aggression, and when is the target of intergroup aggression access to females rather than other material resources. </para></item>
    
