      <para id="id1168598135229">This article examines collective aggression as perpetuated by young adult males aged between 15 and 30 years. It proposes that such behavior is a fitness-enhancing behavior. It then compares this model to the correlation of a large population of young adult males and inter- and intra-state aggression.</para></item>
     
